              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USANOT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " FN tandem accelerator was used to",
                "accelerate radioactive 6Li beam"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural Ni targets were used, with thicknesses",
                "between 1.36 and 5.60 and target sizes",
                "    thickness (mg/cm2)     size (cm)",
                "           1.36           2.5 diameter",
                "           2.22           8.9 x 8.9",
                "           5.60            13 x 13"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections were applied to account for the presence",
                "of isotopes other than 58 Ni."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Silicon surface-barrier detectors",
                "were used for the backward telescopes and for the",
                "beam monitors. The thin (dE) detectors of the",
                "backward telescopes were 65-95 mu-m thick for stage 1,",
                "while they had a typical thickness of cca 40 mu-m for",
                "all other stages. The thick (E) detectors had a",
                "thickness of cca 1000 mu-m thick for all",
                "measurements. Solid angles were defined by",
                "collimators of 18-25 mm in diameter placed in front",
                "of all telescopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A primary 6Li3+ high-intensity beam with energies",
                "between 31 and 38 MeV, delivered by the UND FN tandem",
                "accelerator, was used to bombard a 2.5-cm- long",
                "primary gas target of 3He at a pressure of 1 atm.",
                "Secondary beam rates of (0.6-4.0)E+7 particles/s were",
                "typically achieved. The respective energy resolution",
                "was 0.6-0.8 MeV FWHM, with a typical time spread of",
                "7-10 ns. 6Li beam could be nicely separated by TOF",
                "from the other major components, except satellite",
                "4He2+ beam, with relative yield of 0.4%, which can be",
                "safely neglected."
              ]
            }
          ],
